Program 1: Simulating a File Download with Callbacks
=====================================================
Aim: To practice using callbacks to handle asynchronous file download 
                                          simulation.
Task Description:
====================
=>Create a function that simulates downloading a file 
                     (use setTimeout to mimic a delay of 3 seconds).
=>Pass a callback function that executes after the download completes, 
      displaying the file name and size (e.g., "file.txt", 5MB).
=>Write a second callback to log a message confirming the file was saved
                          to a folder.
=>Test the program by calling the download function with different file 
                        names and sizes.
Challenge: Add error handling if the file size is negative or invalid.


Program 2: Fetching Student Data with Promises
===============================================
Aim: To practice creating and resolving Promises for fetching student 
                                                                 data.
Task Description:
=================
=>Write a function that returns a Promise to fetch student 
            data (e.g., roll number and name) after a 2-second delay.
=>If the roll number is valid (e.g., positive), resolve the Promise
  with the student object; otherwise, reject it with an error message.
=>Consume the Promise using .then() to display the student data 
                       and .catch() to handle errors.
=>Test with both valid and invalid roll numbers.

Challenge: Chain another Promise to fetch the student’s grades based 
on the roll number.


Program 3: Sequential API Calls with Promise Chaining
=======================================================
Aim: To practice chaining Promises to perform sequential asynchronous
                                                        operations.
Task Description:
===============

=>Create two functions: one that returns a Promise to fetch a user’s
 profile (e.g., user ID and name) and another to fetch their course 
 list based on the user ID.
=>Use setTimeout to simulate API delays (e.g., 1 second for profile, 
                      2 seconds for courses).
=>Chain the Promises to first fetch the profile and then the 
           course list, displaying both results.
=>Include error handling for cases where the user ID is invalid.

Challenge: Add a third Promise to fetch course details 
           (e.g., course name and credits) for one of the courses.


Program 4: Fetching Library Books with Async/Await
==================================================
Aim: To practice using async/await for cleaner asynchronous code.
Task Description:

=>Write a function that returns a Promise to fetch book details
 (e.g., book ID, title, and availability) after a 1-second delay.
=>Create an async function that uses await to fetch details of a 
           single book and display its title and availability status.
=>Use a try/catch block to handle errors if the book ID is invalid.
=>Test with multiple book IDs, including one that fails.

Challenge: Modify the function to fetch details of two books 
sequentially and display both results.


Program 5: Parallel Data Fetching with Promise.all
===================================================
Aim: To practice using Promise.all to handle multiple Promises 
              concurrently.
Task Description:
=================
=>Create a function that returns a Promise to fetch product 
details (e.g., product ID and name) after a random delay (1-3 seconds).
=>Write an async function that uses Promise.all to fetch details of 
 three products concurrently.
=>Display the results as a list of product names.
=>Include error handling to catch cases where any product ID is invalid.

Challenge: Add a condition where one Promise intentionally rejects to 
test error handling.


Program 6: Simulating a Login System with Async/Await
======================================================
Aim: To practice error handling in asynchronous operations using
                                                         async/await.
Task Description:
=================
=>Create a function that returns a Promise to simulate user 
    login (e.g., check username and password) with a 1-second delay.
=>Resolve the Promise with a success message if credentials are
  valid (e.g., username: "student", password: "pass123"); otherwise,
   reject with an error.
=>Write an async function that uses await to call the login function 
                and display the result.
=>Use try/catch to handle login failures.
=>Test with both valid and invalid credentials.
Challenge: Add a second Promise to fetch user preferences after 
              a successful login.

